  <title>SLT receives the BOI status</title>
  <link>https://www.slt.lk/en/announcements/slt-receives-boi-status</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;SLT receives the BOI status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;span lang="" about="https://www.slt.lk/en/user/16" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" xml:lang=""&gt;osandacm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Thu, 06/02/2022 - 14:59&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-announcement field--type-text-with-summary field--label-above"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Announcement&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Corporate Disclosure - Sri Lanka Telecom Ltd&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In terms of Sec. 9.1 (ii) of the Disclosure Requirements under the CSE Rules, we write to disclose that Sri Lanka Telecom Ltd. has been granted approval under Section 17 of the BOI Law.&lt;br /&gt;
In terms of this approval given by their letter dated 14.5.2007, all future imports of capital goods and telecommunication equipment by the Company will be free of customs duty.&lt;br /&gt;
Shoji Takahashi&lt;br /&gt;
CEO-SLT&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
